      • addUniformNoiseToImage

        public static ImageTTAA addUniformNoiseToImage(ImageTTAA img,
                                               double intervalLength,
                                               double center)
        Adds uniformly distributed additive noise to an image. New pixel value becomes: u(i,j) = u(i,j) + U(c-L/2,c+L/2), where U is a uniformly distributed random variable, c is the specified center offset, and L is the interval length.
        Parameters:
        img - input image
        intervalLength - size of uniform interval to draw samples from
        center - middle of the interval of the additive noise
        Returns:
